"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-diana-taurasi-paris-games-last-olympics\", \"text\": \"In this story:  Phoenix Mercury star Diana Taurasi broke some major news ahead of the United States women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic basketball team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s opener in the 2024 Paris Games.  Taurasi was asked whether this summer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympics was \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cit\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d for her, and the three-time WNBA champion didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t beat around the bush.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s definitely it for USA Basketball,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Taurasi said. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m 42. Six Olympics. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just been such an honor to put that jersey on every single time.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The 2024 Paris Olympics will be her last Olympic Games, Diana Taurasi announced.\\\"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m 42. Six Olympics. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just been such an honor to put that jersey on every single time.\\\" \\u00f0\\u009f\\u008fpic.twitter.com/JX9BtyAIYt  Taurasi, 42, was selected to her record sixth Olympic squad earlier this summer and will be looking to become the first men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s or women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball player to win six gold medals. The Mercury All-Star guard averaged 10.9 points, 3.0 rebounds and 2.6 assists throughout the last five Olympic competitions and is currently the all-time leader in games played at the Olympics with 38. Taurasi is ranked fourth on the Olympics all-time leading scorers list with 414 points.  Taurasi, a 2009 MVP, is in the middle of her 20th WNBA season and adds an undeniable veteran presence on a Team USA roster stacked with talented stars and playmakers including A\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ja Wilson, Breanna Stewart and Kelsey Plum, among others.  Team USA has never lost an Olympic game in which Taurasi was playing, though that win streak goes all the way back to the 1992 Barcelona Games, 12 years before Taurasi\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic debut.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m just as addicted to basketball right now as I was when I was 15 playing in my driveway,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Taurasi said earlier this month. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have the same ambitions, the same passion, the same love for it. I show up every single day in Phoenix at the practice facility at 7:30 a.m. ready to go. That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s how I treat it. However, when it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s done it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s done.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Four years from now, Taurasi may still be spotted in Los Angeles, the host city for the 2028 Games, but chances areshe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be enjoying a beer on the beach instead.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Kristen Wong is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated. She has been a sports journalist since 2020 and has a bachelor\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in English and linguistics from Columbia University. Before joining SI in November 2023, Wong covered four NFL teams as an associate editor with the FanSided NFL network and worked as a staff writer for the brand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s flagship site. She is a lifelong Liverpool fan who enjoys solving crossword puzzles and hanging out at her neighborhood dive bar in NYC.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"